prompts.prompt:
Act as a LinkedIn content strategist. Write a high-performing post about: {{topic}}

Industry: {{industry}}
Personal angle: {{personal_angle}}
Goal: {{goal}}

Post structure:
Line 1 (HOOK): Single sentence. Make them click 'see more'.
Lines 2-4: Set up the tension or story
Lines 5-12: The insight or value (use white space)
Line 13-15: The takeaway in simple terms
Line 16 (CTA): One clear ask
3-5 relevant hashtags at the bottom

Target: 200-300 words total. Short sentences.

Act as an Instagram content strategist. Write 3 caption options for a post about: {{post_topic}}

Niche: {{niche}}
Visual description: {{visual_description}}
Goal: {{goal}}

For each caption:
- Opening line (stop the scroll with words alone)
- Story or context (2-4 sentences)
- Value/insight (why they'll save it)
- Question or CTA
- 15-20 hashtags (3 large, 7 medium, 5 niche, 3 brand)

Rank from most to least likely to go viral. Explain why #1 wins.

Act as a case study writer. Create a compelling case study:

Client type: {{client_type}}
Situation before: {{situation_before}}
Service provided: {{service}}
Results: {{results}}
Timeframe: {{timeframe}}

Structure:
1. HEADLINE: Result-focused, specific numbers
2. SUBHEADLINE: Who + what + how fast
3. THE CHALLENGE: Relatable pain and urgency
4. THE SOLUTION: What you did, why it worked
5. THE RESULTS: Quantified + emotional impact
6. THE TURNING POINT: The moment everything changed
7. CLIENT QUOTE: 3 quote options for client to choose
8. CTA: 'Could this work for you too?'

Write as narrative, not a report.

Act as an instructional designer. Build a full outline for a course on: {{course_topic}}

Target student: {{target_student}}
Desired transformation: {{transformation}}
Price point: {{price}}
Delivery format: {{format}}

Deliver:
1. Course title (5 options, benefit-focused)
2. Course promise/transformation statement
3. 8-12 module structure: module title, core objective, 3-5 lessons, key exercise
4. Bonus materials (3-5 ideas)
5. Community/support component
6. Quick-win lesson in Module 1 (reduces refunds)
7. Course sales hook: 'By the end of Module 1, you will...'

Design for completion, not just enrollment.

Act as a launch strategist. Create a complete 14-day launch plan for: {{product}} at {{price}}

Audience size: {{audience_size}}
Launch channels: {{channels}}
Revenue goal: ${{revenue_goal}}

Deliver:
1. Pre-launch (Days 1-7): Content calendar, email sequence (3 emails), social proof collection
2. Launch week (Days 8-12): Day-by-day email calendar with subject lines, social content
3. Close (Days 13-14): Last 48h urgency sequence, cart close email
4. Revenue projection model
5. What to do if sales are slow mid-launch

Give me a day-by-day execution plan.

Act as an operations manager. Create a detailed SOP for: {{process}}

Role responsible: {{role}}
Frequency: {{frequency}}
Tools involved: {{tools}}

SOP structure:
1. PURPOSE: Why this process exists
2. SCOPE: Who does this, when, with what authority
3. PREREQUISITES: What must be in place before starting
4. STEP-BY-STEP: For each step: what to do, how to do it, expected output, common mistake
5. QUALITY CHECK: How to verify it was done correctly
6. ESCALATION PATH: What to do when something goes wrong
7. METRICS: How to measure if this process is working

Write at a level a new hire could follow on day one.

Act as an HR strategist. Write a hiring post for: {{role}}

Business type: {{business_type}}
Location: {{location}}
Budget: {{budget}}
Hours: {{hours}}

Post structure:
1. HEADLINE: Role + what makes this different
2. WHO WE ARE (2-3 sentences)
3. THE ROLE: Day-to-day activities
4. WHAT GREAT LOOKS LIKE: Deliverables in 30/60/90 days
5. MUST-HAVES: Non-negotiables
6. NICE-TO-HAVES
7. WHAT YOU'LL GET: Compensation + growth
8. HOW TO APPLY: Instructions that filter low-effort candidates

Include one secret instruction to weed out copy-pasters.

Act as an automation architect. Design a complete automation workflow for: {{process}}

Tools I use: {{tools}}
Volume: {{volume}} per {{frequency}}
Time spent manually: {{manual_time}}
Platform preference: {{platform}}

Deliver:
1. CURRENT STATE MAP: Manual process steps
2. AUTOMATION ANALYSIS: Which steps to automate and why
3. AUTOMATION BLUEPRINT: Trigger, action sequence, conditions, error handling
4. TOOL STACK: Specific tool for each step
5. IMPLEMENTATION PLAN: Build in phases
6. TIME SAVINGS: Hours per week/month
7. MONITORING: Alerts if it breaks

Build this so it runs without me.

Act as an AI image prompt engineer. Create prompts for: {{concept}}

Tool: {{ai_tool}}
Style: {{style}}
Use case: {{use_case}}

Create 5 prompt variations:
1. PHOTOREALISTIC: Cinematic quality
2. ILLUSTRATIVE: Design/art-forward
3. MINIMALIST: Clean, simple composition
4. DRAMATIC: High contrast, emotional impact
5. COMMERCIAL: Ready for marketing use

For each prompt include: subject description, setting, lighting, camera/perspective, art style references, color palette, technical parameters, negative prompts.

Make each copy-paste ready.

Act as an AI systems architect. Design a complete AI workflow for: {{goal}}

Available tools: {{tools}}
Input: {{input_type}}
Desired output: {{output_type}}
Volume: {{volume}} per {{frequency}}

Design:
1. WORKFLOW MAP: Step-by-step flow
2. FOR EACH STEP: Tool, prompt/instruction, input/output, quality check, fallback
3. HUMAN CHECKPOINTS: Where to review before continuing
4. AUTOMATION OPTIONS: Which steps run without human review
5. COST ESTIMATE: Approximate tokens/API cost per run
6. TIME SAVINGS vs. manual workflow
7. SAMPLE OUTPUT: What a completed run looks like

Optimize for quality and speed.

Act as a freelance business advisor. Help me calculate and justify my rates for {{service}}.

My target annual income: ${{annual_income}}
Billable hours available per week: {{billable_hours}}
Business expenses monthly: ${{expenses}}
Years of experience: {{experience}}
Niche specialization: {{niche}}

Calculate:
1. MINIMUM VIABLE RATE: What I must charge to cover costs + income
2. MARKET RATE: What others with similar skills charge (provide range)
3. PREMIUM RATE: What I could charge with strong positioning
4. VALUE-BASED RATE: What the outcome is worth to the client
5. RECOMMENDED RATE: What to charge now, what to target in 6 months
6. HOW TO JUSTIFY IT: Script for explaining your rate confidently
7. RATE INCREASE PLAN: How to raise rates with existing clients

Be specific with numbers.
